                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <ab type="script">15th-century script</ab>
                        <date notBefore="1434" notAfter="1468"/>
                        <desc>
                           Some paleographic features: 
                           ሎ has the loop marking the 7th order attached directly to the body of the letter, without the linking line 
                           (cp. <bibl>
                              <ptr target="bm:Uhlig1988Palaographie"/>
                              <citedRange unit="page">346-347</citedRange>
                           </bibl>); 
                           the upper part of some letters, e.g. ዐ, የ, ደ, ጸ, ቆ, ቶ has a triangular shape; 
                           the left stroke of some letters, e.g. ሰ, በ, ዘ, is slanted; 
                           the loop marking the 5th order of some letters, e.g. በ, ሐ, ቀ, is open (cp. <bibl>
                              <ptr target="bm:Uhlig1988Palaographie"/>
                              <citedRange unit="page">340</citedRange>, <citedRange unit="page">346-347</citedRange>
                           </bibl>); 
                           the crux ansata is used  (cp. <bibl>
                              <ptr target="bm:Uhlig1988Palaographie"/>
                              <citedRange unit="page">330</citedRange>
                           </bibl>).
                        </desc>
